name: Zino's Petrel
rangeDescription: Breeds in summer in cliffs high on pico do arieiro (central madeira; central macaronesia); non-breeding range in subtropical and tropical atlantic to azores (northwestern macaronesia) and st. helena and northeastern brazil (tropical south atlantic ocean)
description: Medium-sized gadfly petrel with long, angular wings and buoyant, banking flight. Extremely similar to Cape Verde and Desertas Petrels (formerly known together as Fea’s), but slightly smaller and more compact overall with a smaller bill.

name: Yellow-throated Serin
rangeDescription: Savanna of ethiopia (shoa province)
description: A very plain gray-brown seedeater with a pale yellow throat and a yellow rump that is conspicuous in flight. The yellow on the throat can be washed out and almost invisible.

name: Tanimbar Megapode
rangeDescription: Tanimbar islands (banda sea)
description: A large, dull-colored partridge-like bird with powerful legs and feet, an obvious crest, and pink facial skin. Shy.

name: Abyssinian Woodpecker
rangeDescription: Savanna and juniper highlands of ethiopia and eritrea
description: A small, short-tailed woodpecker of the Abyssinian highlands. Note the pure golden-green back and the white facial streaks that frame a dark cheek.

name: Philippine Serpent-Eagle
rangeDescription: Forest of larger philippines (except palawan)
description: A fairly large, common raptor of forest and more open wooded areas from the lowlands to the lower mountains. Dark brown with white speckles on the crown and upperparts, rufous-brown below with large white spots.

name: Bounty Islands Shag
rangeDescription: Bounty islands (new zealand)
description: A large pink-footed marine shag endemic to the Bounty Islands and surrounding coastal seas. Adults are black above with a blue sheen, white below, with white patches on upper wings visible in flight.

name: Canada Warbler
rangeDescription: Eastern north america; winters panama and mountains of northwestern south america
description: Spiffy warbler found in boggy areas. Blue-gray above and yellow below with distinctive yellow spectacles and necklace of black streaks.

name: Peruvian Antpitta
rangeDescription: East slope of andes of southeastern ecuador and far northern peru
description: Small, very rare antpitta of Andean cloud forest understory. Despite its name, most sightings are from the east slope of the Andes in Ecuador.

name: Gray Falcon
rangeDescription: Sparse in arid and semiarid areas of australia with scattered trees
description: Seldom-seen pale gray falcon of inland Australia found in arid grassland and woodland habitats, where it sometimes perches high on communication towers. Pale gray upperparts and white underparts, with faint dark streaks below.

name: Sri Lanka White-eye
rangeDescription: Montane forest of sri lanka
description: A small, greenish white-eye, with a bold white eye ring and yellow throat. Usually encountered in active flocks within the canopy of forest and neighboring wooded areas in the hills and mountains.

name: Yellow-breasted Tailorbird
rangeDescription: East-central philippines (bohol, leyte, and samar)
description: A small, long-billed, long-tailed bird of dense undergrowth in lowland forest on Bohol, Leyte, and Samar islands. Olive-green on the back and wings, with an orange-brown tail often held cocked, yellow underparts, a thin yellow line around the back of the neck, and a black cap.

name: Barred Dove
rangeDescription: Southeastern moluccas and lesser sundas
description: A small, long-tailed dove with extensive barring over its body. Pale gray head with distinctive orange eye-ring.

name: Kenya Rufous Sparrow
rangeDescription: Kenya and tanzania
description: A typical sparrow with a striped back, a gray crown and nape, and a dark bib. The rufous rump is conspicuous in flight.

name: Erect-crested Penguin
rangeDescription: Subantarctic new zealand and australian waters
description: Medium-sized crested penguin, endemic to New Zealand. Note the distinct broad yellow eyebrow rising over the eye to form a stiff brush-like crest.

name: Taliabu Myzomela
rangeDescription: Taliabu island (sula islands)
description: Small and distinctive honeyeater with a short and decurved bill, endemic to the montane forests of Taliabu. Male is strikingly beautiful, bright red overall with black wings, belly, and tail.

name: Forster's Tern
rangeDescription: North america; winters southern usa to costa rica and greater antilles
description: Smaller than all the gulls, with thinner and more pointed bill. Distinguished from other terns by pale whitish wings and orange-based bill in summer, and isolated black ear patch in winter.

name: Rufous-webbed Brilliant
rangeDescription: Andean foothills of eastern peru and (?) northwestern bolivia
description: Large, green hummingbird of montane forest. Males have a small red throat patch; females are duller green with a white-speckled belly.

name: Sichuan Bush Warbler
rangeDescription: Breeds in southern china (shaanxi, sichuan, guizhou, hubei, northwestern hunan, and northwestern jiangxi); nonbreeding range unknown
description: Drab brown warbler of hilly central China; russet-brown above and cold gray-brown below, with dark stripes on the vent. Like many other bush warblers, very difficult to see as it skulks deep in dense vegetation; typically prefers to scurry or run instead of fly to reach cover.

name: Cassin's Spinetail
rangeDescription: Sierra leone and liberia to northwestern angola and western uganda; bioko
description: A distinctive swift of lowland forest that appears nearly tailless. The wings appear “pinched” at the body but are otherwise fairly straight and broad.

name: Little Sparrowhawk
rangeDescription: Forest and thornscrub of eastern and southern africa
description: A tiny, secretive and inconspicuous hawk that flies quickly and nimbly within woodland thickets and forest while hunting small birds, other vertebrates, and insects. It has a very distinctive white rump and two pale spots on the upper tail.
